name: Guardian International Equity Select Fund
longDescription: Fund invest primarily in securities of mid- to large-size international companies that have a track record of paying and growing dividends. International markets are defined as those countries included in the MSCI EAFE Index. Securities are selected primarily from developed markets, but the Fund may invest in emerging market securities. The primary objective of the Fund is the achievement of a high level of stable income, with an attractive total return.
